modules.description: This module defines and parses cursor index entry types, distinguishing between comments (with subtypes like copyright or license) and image references. It provides parsers for comment subtypes, image entries, and the overall index type. Used to process cursor file metadata, identifying specific entry kinds like comments or images within the file structure.

Parses 32-bit unsigned integers from cursor files using Angstrom. It supports reading both fixed and variable-length card32 values. This is used for decoding binary cursor file data, such as image dimensions and delay times.

This module defines the structure and parsing logic for cursor image headers. It provides a fixed-length header type and a parser to read binary cursor image data. Used to load and interpret cursor image metadata from Xcursor files.

Handles parsing and representation of cursor file index entries, including their types and positions. Works with index entry types and file position data to locate and categorize cursor images and metadata. Used to navigate cursor files by identifying where specific elements like images or comments are stored.

Handles low-level cursor image data parsing and header manipulation. Works with binary cursor image data and header structures to extract metadata and image dimensions. Used for loading and interpreting Xcursor file contents directly.

Handles parsing and representation of cursor file headers, including version and table of contents. Works with header data structures containing version numbers and index entries. Used to read and interpret the structure of cursor files by extracting metadata and locating image data.

Handles 32-bit unsigned integer values for cursor file data, including parsing and manipulation. Works directly with binary cursor file formats to extract and process image dimensions, animation delays, and other metadata. Used in decoding and constructing cursor images and their associated timing information.

This module parses and manipulates Xcursor file data, handling operations such as reading headers, extracting image indices, and retrieving image data from memory-mapped files or bigstrings. It works with binary cursor file structures, including headers, image metadata, and raw image data. Concrete use cases include loading cursor themes, extracting animated cursor frames, and inspecting cursor file contents for rendering or conversion tools.

This module handles parsing and manipulation of Xcursor binary files, providing operations to read headers, extract image indices, and retrieve raw image data from memory-mapped files or bigstrings. It works directly with binary cursor file structures, including header metadata and image data chunks. Use cases include loading cursor themes, extracting frames from animated cursors, and inspecting cursor contents for rendering or conversion tools.
